&lt;li&gt;You are deeply blockchain-native - you understand EOAs, multisig architecture, signing flows, and the evolution of multi-party signing infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You understand the security failure modes of frontend-driven contract interactions: blind signing, ABI spoofing, malicious frontends, and why these are existential risks in crypto.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience building blockchain-adjacent products - wallets, signing infrastructure, security tooling, or developer-facing crypto products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a product instinct for security - you know how to make the safe path the easy path without removing capability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 3–6+ years of PM experience shipping real products, ideally in crypto, security, or developer tooling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A CS degree or engineering background is a plus; what matters most is whether you can engage at the technical level this product demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think like an owner; you drive work forward without authority or perfect information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable in fast-moving, low-process environments and thrive in ambiguity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
